Bismillah. 

Happy first birthday to my beautiful miracle baby Musa. A year has passed and you are no longer a baby but officially a toddler. 🤯 this last year has been such a roller coaster for all of us, subhanAllah. We’ve been through more “firsts” than we can count.

I could never imagine through such a horrible pregnancy last year that this is what my life with you would be like. That I’d constantly crave your loving slobbery kisses and aggressive full body slam hugs. That I think of you first, second, and third before thinking of anyone else. That my heart would somehow double, triple in size to contain all of the love I have for you. That I look forward to seeing you after every nap and goodnight. That your smile makes my heart ache with so much joy. That with every new milestone you hit I feel just a pinch of sadness that you grow so much every day and aren’t going to stay small and little inside my arms forever. That being a boy mom would teach me so much about being a strong and powerful woman. Being a mother is wild. It’s simultaneously feeling so many things all at once. It’s pure exhaustion and pure joy. It’s being incredibly touched out but also incredibly full of affection. It’s wanting to constantly be overprotective but also wanting your child to taste independence. It’s getting to live vicariously through your inner child and also living the most authentic big girl version of yourself. It’s feeling on edge a lot of times but also the safest space for your child. It’s feeling uncertain about so much, but confident in so much more. 

It’s feeling powerful. It’s feeling kindness. It’s feeling love to a whole new degree. 

Happy first birthday to Mr. Musa. Welcome to toddlerhood. May you continue to live your life with laughter and smiles. May your world be filled with more love and joy than you could ever imagine. May you be strong and steadfast through anything this life throws at you. May your fire continue to burn so bright. May your big eyes always see the beauty in the world. May your innocence always inspire others. May you always remember your Mama is your safe harbor. InshaAllah 

Forever& always 💗
